        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 4:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 13:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Israel could not match these with corresponding forces (compare ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 17:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " note and references), but, having the God of battles on its side, was not to be dismayed by them; the assumption being that the war had the sanction of God, and was consequently just. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
